  "highlights": [
    {
      "changeIds": [
        "pr:nightscout/Trio#1200"
      ],
      "summary": "Removes legacy OmniBLE/OmniKit submodules and platform-specific code paths and consolidates Omnipod support under OmnipodKit/OmniPumpManager. Replaces OmniBLEPumpManager/OmnipodPumpManager usages with OmniPumpManager, collapses separate \"Omnipod Eros\"/\"Omnipod DASH\" UI options into a single Omnipod entry, merges onboarding enum cases into a single .omni/.omnipod case (with an inline FIXME noting Eros' minimum basal-rate handling), and updates project/workspace targets, localization sources, build scripts, and telemetry/privacy references. Also bumps the OmnipodKit submodule.",
      "userFacingImpact": "UI: Pump-selection buttons are collapsed to a single Omnipod entry / label changes in Home and PumpConfig (file:a3b74c4d866b; file:5594b79c883d; file:81981acd73f2). Onboarding: the Omnipod basal-rate picker now uses a single .omni case and currently uses the DASH minimum (0 U/hr) even though Eros requires a 0.05 U/hr minimum — an inline FIXME records this gap (file:50ec6c64aeb9; pr:nightscout/Trio#1200; diff:e8826da257ca). Build/developer: OmniBLE/OmniKit submodules, targets, and workspace references were removed and OmnipodKit was bumped, which affects repository submodules and Xcode project/workspace configuration (file:cf03e8273754; file:07751cf172bd; file:f6494ea0313b; commit:cf0209a1c793adb215764f087c7bc5e6df147643). Potential safety concern: the inability to distinguish Eros vs DASH at the onboarding basal-rate step could allow an Eros user to set a 0 U/hr minimum when Eros requires 0.05 U/hr — this is noted in the change and should be reviewed by a human (file:50ec6c64aeb9; pr:nightscout/Trio#1200).",
      "category": "interface-improvements",
